    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-01-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-03-01T15:36:42Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Prohibits any official of the Department of Defense (DOD) from entering into a contract with, or otherwise procuring any property or services from, a person under investigation by the DOD Inspector General, unless the selection of such person for such contract or procurement is made with full and open competition.</p> <p>Authorizes the President to waive such prohibition when determined necessary to U.S. national security interests, requiring at least 15 days' advance notification to Congress.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to limit Department of Defense contracting with firms under investigation by the Inspector General of the Department of Defense.</title>
